Class ProcessorStaticState

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.upmc.datacenter.hardware.processors.ProcessorStaticState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    fr.upmc.components.interfaces.DataOfferedI.DataI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.DataRequiredI.DataI, ProcessorStaticStateI, TimeStampingI, java.io.Serializable

    public class ProcessorStaticState
extends java.lang.Object
implements ProcessorStaticStateI
    The class ProcessorStaticState implements objects representing a snapshot of the static state of a processor component to be pulled or pushed through the dynamic state data interface.

        create a snapshot of the static state of a processor component.

        Contract

         pre    numberOfCores > 0
 pre    admissibleFrequencies != null && forall i in admissibleFrequencies, i > 0
 pre    admissibleFrequencies.contains(defaultFrequency)
 pre    processingPower != null && forall i in processingPower.values(), i > 0
 post   true                    // no postcondition.
        Parameters:
        numberOfCores - number of cores of the processor.
        defaultFrequency - default frequency at which the cores run.
        maxFrequencyGap - max frequency gap among cores of the same processor.
        admissibleFrequencies - admissible frequencies for cores.
        processingPower - Mips for the different admissible frequencies.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
